2 shot, including 13-year-old girl

SHOOTING April 15, 2021, 11:40 p.m.
Location: 400 block of Buttonwood St., Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

A 13-year-old girl was one of two people shot in Wilmington's Southbridge neighborhood.

Wilmington police did not provide the medical conditions of the girl or a 24-year-old man shot about 11:40 p.m. Thursday in the 400 block of Buttonwood St., other than to say they were stable.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Girl, 13

Unidentified Man, 24

2 shot in Prices Run neighborhood late Wednesday

SHOOTING April 14, 2021, 9:55 p.m.
Location: 2300 block of Carter St., Wilmington, DE 19802

Incident summary:

A double shooting in Wilmington's Prices Run neighborhood late Wednesday has left a 22-year-old woman in critical condition.

Wilmington Police did not provide a medical condition for a 46-year-old man also wounded in Wednesday's shooting, other than to say that man was stable.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Woman, 22 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

3 women shot, 1 fatally

HOMICIDE April 13, 2021, 2 p.m.
Location: In the area of 1000 block of North Pine St., Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

One woman was killed and two others were injured in an afternoon triple shooting in Wilmington's East Side section, police said.

The incident occurred just after 2 p.m. in the area of 10th and Pine streets, where more than 20 evidence markers later dotted the street as police investigated.

Killed in the incident was 37-year-old Latahesia Hill. Also injured were a 26-year-old woman and a 23-year-old woman.

Victims: Suspects:
Latahesia Hill, 37 (killed)

Unidentified Woman, 26

Unidentified Woman, 23 		Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Man, 44, shot dead in Brandywine Village

HOMICIDE April 2, 2021, 9 p.m.
Location: In the area of 200 block of W. 19th St., Wilmington, DE 19802

Incident summary:

A 44-year-old man was killed during a shooting in Brandywine Village, Wilmington police said.

Police said the shooting occurred just after 9 p.m. in the 200 block of W. 19th St. The victim was taken to the hospital, where he died.

Police later identified him as Larry Porter.

Victims: Suspects:
Larry Porter, 44 (killed) Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Man, 21, shot in Hedgeville

SHOOTING March 30, 2021, 5:55 p.m.
Location: In the area of 200 block of Maryland Ave., Wilmington, DE 19805

Incident summary:

A 21-year-old man was shot near Wilmington's Hedgeville section.

Police said the shooting happened just before 6 p.m. in the 200 block of Maryland Ave.

The man was found at the scene and taken to an area hospital, where he was listed in stable condition, according to police.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Woman, 30 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Woman stable after being shot

SHOOTING March 29, 2021, 5:30 p.m.
Location: In the area of Lancaster Avenue and Clayton Street, Wilmington, DE 19805

Incident summary:

Police are investigating a shooting in Wilmington's Bayard Square neighborhood.

In a press release, Wilmington police said a shooting occurred around 5:30 p.m. in the area of Lancaster Avenue and Clayton Street.

A 30-year-old woman was hospitalized in stable condition, police said.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 21 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Teen shot in Southbridge

SHOOTING March 29, 2021, 2:45 a.m.
Location: In the area of 400 block of Bradford St., Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

A 19-year-old man was critically wounded after being shot in Wilmington's Southbridge neighborhood.

City police provided few details about the shooting other than it occurred about 2:45 a.m. in the 400 block of Bradford St. Police also said the teen was taken to an area hospital in critical condition.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 19 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Man, 28, killed in West Center City

HOMICIDE March 16, 2021, 8:35 p.m.
Location: In the area of 700 block of N. Washington St., Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

A 28-year-old man died after being shot in Wilmington's West Center City, police said.

Police were called to the 700 block of N. Washington St. just after 8:30 p.m. for reports of a shooting.

There, police found Demier Chambers injured. Paramedics took him to a local hospital, where he died.

Victims: Suspects:
Demier Chambers, 28 (killed)

Man, 28 shot in West Center City

SHOOTING March 15, 2021, 11:50 a.m.
Location: In the area of Fourth and Adams streets, Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

A 28-year-old man was shot in West Center City about 11:50 a.m. near Fourth and Adams streets.

Officers blocked off a section of the 1000 block of W. Fourth St. near North Van Buren St. and were seen investigating near a light-blue sedan facing eastbound traffic. The hood of the car was smashed, its trunk was open and the car's airbags appeared to have deployed

Police said the man was taken to the hospital and is in "stable condition."

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 28

Man, 42, shot in Riverside neighborhood

SHOOTING March 8, 2021, 5:20 p.m.
Location: In the area of 1300 block of E. 27th St., Wilmington, DE 19802

Incident summary:

A 42-year-old man was treated after being shot in Wilmington's Riverside area.

The shooting occurred about 5:20 p.m. in the 1300 block of E. 27th St., Wilmington Police said.

After police found the wounded man in the Riverside public housing community, he was taken to an area hospital, where police reported him to be stable.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 42 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Man, 20, shot in East Side

SHOOTING March 1, 2021, noon
Location: In the area of East 26th Street and Northeast Boulevard, Wilmington, DE 19802

Incident summary:

A 20-year-old man who was shot on Wilmington's East Side is the ninth person in five days to have been injured by gunfire in Delaware.

Wilmington police said the shooting occurred near the intersection of E. 26th Street and Northeast Boulevard at noon. The man showed up at a local hospital, where he was stable.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 20 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Two women shot, one fatally

HOMICIDE Feb. 25, 2021, 7:10 p.m.
Location: In the area of 600 block of E. 22nd St., Wilmington, DE 19802

Incident summary:

A 43-year-old woman fatally shot Thursday night in Wilmington has been identified by police as Levonne Kellam.

Kellam and a 50-year-old woman were shot about 7:10 p.m. Thursday in the 600 block of E. 22nd St. – in the city's Price Run section. The older woman survived the shooting, police said.

Victims: Suspects:
Levonne Kellam, 43 (killed)

Unidentified Woman, 50 		Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Woman shot on East Side

SHOOTING Feb. 21, 2021, 9:50 p.m.
Location: In the area of 500 block of E. Sixth St., Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

A 21-year-old woman was shot Sunday night in the city's East Side community.

Wilmington Police provided few details in the woman's shooting, other than to say it occurred about 9:50 p.m. in the 500 block of E. Sixth St.

The woman arrived at the hospital on her own, police added.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 21 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Two shot near Trinity Vicinity neighborhhod

SHOOTING Feb. 15, 2021, 11:45 p.m.
Location: In the area of West 10th and North Madison streets, Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

According to Wilmington police and radio scanner traffic, two men — an 18-year-old and a 21-year-old — showed up at a local hospital by private vehicle after being shot near West 10th and North Madison streets Monday night.

Police said that shooting occurred about 11:45 p.m.

The 21-year-old was listed as "stable" while the 18-year-old was in critical condition.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 18

Unidentified Man, 21 		Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Man shot in West Center City critically wounded

SHOOTING Feb. 8, 2021, 9:20 p.m.
Location: In the area of 800 block of West 4th St., Wilmington, DE 19805

Incident summary:

A 23-year-old man was in critical condition after being shot in Wilmington's West Center City neighborhood, according to police.

The shooting took place about 9:20 p.m. in the 800 block of West 4th St. The man was taken to a nearby hospital and was in "critical condition."

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 23 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Man critically wounded in Southbridge shooting

SHOOTING Feb. 7, 2021, 10:55 p.m.
Location: In the area of C and Townsend streets, Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

A 30-year-old man was shot Sunday in the city's Southbridge neighborhood, according to Wilmington Police.

Police said the shooting occurred about 10:55 p.m. near C and Townsend streets. The man was taken to a hospital and was in "critical condition," police said.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 30 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Teen shot in city's Ninth Ward community

SHOOTING Feb. 4, 2021, 5:45 p.m.
Location: In the area of 600 block of W. 27th St., Wilmington, DE 19802

Incident summary:

A 13-year-old boy was shot in Wilmington's Ninth Ward section, police said.

Wilmington police said the shooting occurred at approximately 5:45 p.m. in the 600 block of W. 27th St. The teen was transported to the hospital and listed in stable condition.

No other information was immediately available.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Boy, 13 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Man, 31, shot in Riverside section

SHOOTING Feb. 4, 2021, 1:35 p.m.
Location: In the area of 2800 N. Claymont St., Wilmington, DE 19802

Incident summary:

A 31-year-old man was recovering after being shot in Wilmington's Riverside section, police said.

Police responded to the area of 2800 N. Claymont St. after 1:30 p.m. after a report of shots being fired. They did not locate a victim then. Later, police said the man arrived at a local hospital with at least one gunshot wound. They determined he was shot in the afternoon incident.

No other information was immediately available.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 31 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Man, 24, killed on Wilmington's East Side

HOMICIDE Jan. 29, 2021, 6:45 p.m.
Location: In the area of 900 block of N. Spruce St., Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

A 24-year-old man was fatally shot in Wilmington's East Side section, police said.

Police said the shooting happened around 6:45 p.m. in the 900 block of N. Spruce St.

The man killed has been identified as Damond Emory.

Victims: Suspects:
Damond Emory, 24 (killed)

Man, 28, shot in Price Run neighborhood

SHOOTING Jan. 24, 2021, 1:20 a.m.
Location: 100 block of E. 24th St., Wilmington, DE 19802

Incident summary:

A 28-year-old man was shot in Wilmington's Price Run neighborhood.

The shooting occurred about 1:20 a.m. in the 100 block of E. 24th St., police said. The man was taken to the hospital and listed in "stable condition."

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 28 Suspect(s) have not been identifed.

Man charged with Hilltop shooting

SHOOTING Jan. 16, 2021, 11:35 a.m.
Location: In the area of 1100 block of W. Fifth St., Wilmington, DE 19805

Incident summary:

Police say 36-year-old Luis Torres shot a 46-year-old man just after 11:30 a.m. in the 1100 block of W. Fifth St., near Harrison Street.

Police said the victim was taken to an area hospital where he was listed as stable.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 46 Luis Torres, 36, arrested on Jan. 16, 2021

Man, 22, shot in West Center City

SHOOTING Jan. 14, 2021, 7:50 p.m.
Location: In the area of 800 block of W. Eighth St., Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

A 22-year-old man was shot in Wilmington's West Center City section.

The shooting occurred about 7:50 p.m. in the 800 block of W. Eighth St. The victim was taken to the hospital and is listed in stable condition, police said.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 22

Two shot, one fatally in West Center City

HOMICIDE Jan. 13, 2021, 7:30 p.m.
Location: In the area of 800 block of N. Monroe St., Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

One man was killed and another was injured during a double shooting in Wilmington's West Center City neighborhood.

Police said the shooting occurred around 7:30 p.m. in the 800 block of N. Monroe St.

Nahshon Archie-Eatmon, 22, was found at the scene and taken to an area hospital, where he was pronounced dead. A 28-year-old man was also wounded and is listed in stable condition, police said.

Victims: Suspects:
Nahshon Archie-Eatmon, 22 (killed)

Unidentified Man, 28

Man shot dead by NCCo Police

HOMICIDE Jan. 13, 2021, 1:10 a.m.
Location: In the area of Rosemont Avenue and East 24th Street, Wilmington, DE 19802

Incident summary:

New Castle County police said they shot and killed a person who drove at their officers in Wilmington's Riverside community.

There was also no explanation why New Castle County police were conducting an investigation on the east end of the Riverside public housing units, which are inside the city of Wilmington.

Killed was 30-year-old Lymond Moses of Bear.

Victims: Suspects:
Lymond Moses, 30

Man, 33, state's first homicide

HOMICIDE Jan. 11, 2021, 5:50 p.m.
Location: In the area of 2800 block of North Claymont St., Wilmington, DE 19802

Incident summary:

A 33-year-old man was killed in northeast Wilmington, the state's first homicide of 2021.

He was shot shortly before 6 p.m. in the 2800 block of North Claymont St., in the Riverside neighborhood, according to Wilmington police.

The victim has been identified as Ismail Drummond.

Victims: Suspects:
Ismail Drummond, 33

Man, 33, shot in West Center City

SHOOTING Jan. 4, 2021, 10:15 p.m.
Location: In the area of Seventh and Washington streets, Wilmington, DE 19801

Incident summary:

A 33-year-old man was shot just before 10:15 p.m. at Seventh and Washington streets, Wilmington police said.

The police department, however, has not explained why its officers were concentrating their investigation on a car stopped in the area of Fifth and Washington streets, across the street from Tabernacle Full Gospel Baptist church.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 33

Man shot on Northeast Boulevard

SHOOTING Jan. 2, 2021, 7:30 p.m.
Location: In the area of 2900 block of Northeast Blvd., Wilmington, DE 19802

Incident summary:

A 43-year-old man was hospitalized after being shot on Northeast Boulevard in Wilmington's Riverside section.

The shooting occurred about 7:30 p.m. in the 2900 block of Northeast Blvd. Multiple evidence markers and shattered glass could be seen in the roadway.

Victims: Suspects:
Unidentified Man, 43
